{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
    "chapterNumber": 11,
    "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11",
    "summary": "Source text for Nehemiah 11 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:1",
      "text": "And the chiefs of the people dwelt in Jerusalem: and the rest of the people cast lots, to bring one of every ten to dwell in Jerusalem the holy city, and nine parts in the other cities.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:2",
      "text": "And the people blessed all the men that volunteered to dwell in Jerusalem.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:3",
      "text": "Now these are the chiefs of the province who dwelt in Jerusalem, and in the cities of Juda; every man dwelt in his possession in their cities: Israel, the priests, and the Levites, and the Nathinim, and the children of the servants of Solomon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:4",
      "text": "And there dwelt in Jerusalem some of the children of Juda, and of the children of Benjamin. Of the children of Juda; Athaia son of Azia, the son of Zacharia, the son of Samaria, the son of Saphatia, the son of Maleleel, and some of the sons of Phares;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:5",
      "text": "and Maasia son of Baruch, son of Chalaza, son of Ozia, son of Adaia, son of Joarib, son of Zacharias, son of Seloni.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:6",
      "text": "All the sons of Phares who dwelt in Jerusalem were four hundred and sixty-eight men of might.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:7",
      "text": "And these were the children of Benjamin; Selo son of Mesulam, son of Joad, son of Phadaia, son of Coleia, son of Maasias, son of Ethiel, son of Jesia.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:8",
      "text": "And after him Gebe, Seli, nine hundred and twenty-eight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:9",
      "text": "And Joel son of Zechri was overseer over them: and Juda son of Asana was second in the city.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:10",
      "text": "Of the priests: both Jadia son of Joarib, and Jachin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:11",
      "text": "Saraia, son of Elchia, son of Mesulam, son of Sadduc, son of Marioth, son of Aetoth, was over the house of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:12",
      "text": "And their brethren doing the work of the house were eight hundred and twentytwo: and Adaia son of Jeroam, son of Phalalia, son of Amasi, son of Zacharia, son of Phassur, son of Melchia,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:13",
      "text": "and his brethren, chiefs of families, two hundred and forty-two: and Amasia son of Esdriel, son of Mesarimith, son of Emmer,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:14",
      "text": "and his brethren, mighty men of war, a hundred and twenty-eight: and their overseer was Badiel son of one of the great men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:15",
      "text": "And of the Levites; Samaia, son of Esricam,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:17",
      "text": "Matthanias son of Micha, and Jobeb son of Samui,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:18",
      "text": "two hundred and eighty-four.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:19",
      "text": "And the porters; Acub, Telamin, and their brethren, a hundred and seventy-two.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:22",
      "text": "And the overseer of the Levites was the son of Bani, son of Ozi, son of Asabia, the son of Micha. Of the sons of Asaph the singers some were over the house of God,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:23",
      "text": "For so was the king's commandment concerning them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:24",
      "text": "And Phathaia son of Baseza was in attendance on the king in every matter for the people,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:25",
      "text": "and with regard to villages in their country district: and some of the children of Juda dwelt in Cariatharboc,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:26",
      "text": "and in Jesu,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:27",
      "text": "and in Bersabee:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:30",
      "text": "And their villages were Lachis and her hands: and they pitched their tents in Bersabee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.31",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:31",
      "text": "And the children of Benjamin dwelt from Gabaa to Machmas.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:nehemiah.11.36",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 11:36",
      "text": "And of the Levites there were divisions to Juda and to Benjamin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
